# Prompt Constraint Options

Add optional constraint toggles to improve generated image prompt quality. Based on user's reference prompt, images currently suffer from: border artifacts, text/signatures, paper/table framing, historical inaccuracies, and missing safety rules.

## Proposed Changes

### Constraint Templates

#### [NEW] [prompt_constraints.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_constraints.py)

Central module defining constraint text blocks as constants:

| Constraint | Purpose | Example rules |
|---|---|---|
| `SAFETY` | PG-13, no policy violations | No explicit content, use cinematic implication for sensitive scenes |
| `QUALITY` | Anti-artifact output rules | No text/signatures, no borders, no paper/table framing, borderless full-frame, no split-screen |
| `HISTORICAL` | Era consistency | Architecture, costumes, weapons, vehicles must match the era |

Each is a text block appended to the style's system prompt when enabled.

